---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---
<SiteLayout
  title="About Nathan Bullock — nbdevlab"
  description="Meet Nathan Bullock, the builder behind nbdevlab. Learn about the journey, skills, and how to connect."
>
  <section class="projects-shell" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
    <header>
      <h1 id="about-heading">Hi, I’m Nathan</h1>
      <p>
        I run nbdevlab as a perpetual workshop for edge-native automation, UI systems, and homelab infrastructure. I love pairing
        OpenAI’s tooling with intentional design to ship approachable, resilient products.
      </p>
    </header>

    <article class="card" aria-labelledby="bio-heading">
      <h2 id="bio-heading" class="card__title">Biography</h2>
      <p>
        I started my career as a systems engineer, wiring up VMware clusters and keeping high-availability networks honest. The lab
        quickly became my sandbox for testing failovers, hardening services, and experimenting with automation. Over the years the
        command line made room for TypeScript, Astro, and interface design — the ingredients I use today to build helpful tooling.
      </p>
      <p>
        nbdevlab is where those threads meet. I sketch ideas in notebooks, pair with OpenAI’s Codex to accelerate implementation,
        and deploy to Cloudflare’s edge so experiments stay close to the metal. Every project is an opportunity to learn,
        document, and share.
      </p>
    </article>

    <section aria-labelledby="skills-heading" class="card" role="list">
      <h2 id="skills-heading" class="card__title">Skills snapshot</h2>
      <div class="card-grid" role="list">
        <article class="card" role="listitem">
          <h3 class="card__title">Edge &amp; automation</h3>
          <p>Cloudflare Workers, Durable Objects, KV storage, and TypeScript-first deployment pipelines.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" role="listitem">
          <h3 class="card__title">UI &amp; UX systems</h3>
          <p>Astro, React/Preact islands, accessible navigation, and design systems tuned for dark/light modes.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" role="listitem">
          <h3 class="card__title">Homelab operations</h3>
          <p>Proxmox, TrueNAS, pfSense, observability stacks, and runbooks that keep services resilient.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="timeline-heading" class="card">
      <h2 id="timeline-heading" class="card__title">Highlights</h2>
      <ol class="timeline" role="list">
        <li class="timeline__item" role="listitem">
          <p class="timestamp">2025</p>
          <h3>nbdevlab goes public</h3>
          <p>Rebuilt the site with Astro + Cloudflare Pages, exposing the dashboards and automation powering the lab.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="timeline__item" role="listitem">
          <p class="timestamp">2023</p>
          <h3>Edge-first automation</h3>
          <p>Shifted personal tooling to Workers, Durable Objects, and queue-driven pipelines to remove on-prem bottlenecks.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="timeline__item" role="listitem">
          <p class="timestamp">2019</p>
          <h3>Homelab resilience sprint</h3>
          <p>Overhauled backups, observability, and failover processes after a cascading UPS outage. Wrote the runbooks that still
            guide the lab.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="contact-heading" class="card">
      <h2 id="contact-heading" class="card__title">Let’s connect</h2>
      <ul class="list-reset">
        <li>
          <strong>Email:</strong>
          <a href="mailto:hello@nbdevlab.com">hello@nbdevlab.com</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>GitHub:</strong>
          <a href="https://github.com/0xC0FFEEBEEF" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">0xC0FFEEBEEF ↗</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>LinkedIn:</strong>
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nathan-bullock" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Nathan Bullock ↗</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
